      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Software used for CFD simulation must be verified under a quality management system with documented version control, regression testing, and traceable change logs consistent with MRL 5 requirements.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver has documented unit tests and version control, but formal QMS certification and independent regression test suites required at MRL 5 are absent. Achieved level 2 reflects partial documentation only."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy studies and manufactured solution benchmarks must confirm correct numerical implementation of all governing equations relevant to hemolysis prediction at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy verification was performed for the Navier-Stokes solver on simple geometries. However, the hemolysis transport scalar equation was not subjected to manufactured solution verification, leaving a gap against MRL 5 requirements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Systematic mesh refinement study with Richardson extrapolation and GCI estimates must demonstrate discretization error below 5% on hemolysis index QoI at all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study was completed with GCI estimates reported. Discretization error on hemolysis index exceeded 5% at two of five operating points, falling short of the required threshold for MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions used for validation must match COU operating conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties, temperature) within documented uncertainty bounds at all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "Experimental data were collected at three of five target operating points. Fluid temperature and viscosity were not controlled to match COU conditions at two points, introducing uncharacterised systematic bias in the validation baseline."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E_rel or validation uncertainty interval) must be computed with combined simulation and experimental uncertainty, demonstrating agreement within acceptance band for hemolysis index.",
      "rationale": "Relative error between predicted and measured hemolysis index ranged from 18% to 47% across assessed operating points. Combined uncertainty intervals were computed but validation error exceeds the acceptance band at all assessed points."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoIs used in validation (hemolysis index, shear stress exposure time integral) must directly correspond to the clinical decision QoIs specified in the COU without surrogate substitution.",
      "rationale": "Validation used normalised hemolysis index as the primary QoI, which is directly relevant. However, shear stress exposure time integral — a required secondary QoI under MRL 5 — was not reported in the validation dataset."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry, blood analogue fluid, and operating envelope as the COU. Deviations must be formally justified with similarity arguments.",
      "rationale": "Validation was performed on the FDA generic pump geometry with a glycerol-water blood analogue. The COU specifies patient-specific operating ranges that extend beyond the validated envelope; no formal similarity argument was provided for the extrapolation."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence, round-off error, and solver residual behaviour must be documented and shown to contribute negligibly to overall simulation error budget at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Solver residual convergence criteria were set but not systematically varied to characterise solver error contribution. This factor was flagged as an epistemic gap at MRL 5 and was not assessed in the Morrison study."
    },
