      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented review process must confirm that simulation setup, boundary condition specification, and post-processing were performed without user-introduced errors, with independent verification of key inputs.",
      "rationale": "No independent review of simulation setup was performed. Boundary conditions were set by the primary analyst without cross-check. This factor was identified as an epistemic gap and not formally assessed."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The selected turbulence model and hemolysis damage accumulation model must be justified against alternatives with documented sensitivity analysis demonstrating model form uncertainty is bounded and acceptable for MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "The k-omega SST turbulence model was selected without comparative evaluation against alternative models. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law was used without model form sensitivity analysis. Factor not assessed; flagged as highest-priority epistemic gap."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
